

BNF rule:
for ::= '{' [assignment] ‘^’ [expr] >= 0 ‘^’ [assignment] : block '}' 


We choose this BNF because it is very similar to C. By making the default value >=0 in the condition of for loop, the program is shorter and easy understood.

